Head of Corporate Planning Department Job (Manager) (Life Insurance), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Marketing
Industry:
Insurance
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
30 April 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of a leading joint-venture life insurance company. Our respected client is currently looking for talented and highly motivated professional for the highly valued position of Head of Corporate Planning Department, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will provide expertise, solutions development, analysis support as well as methods to support the development and implementation of analysis solutions and business applications. The successful applicant will serve as a central market research and intelligence function in the company.
Key job responsibilities will include:
Manage, implement and optimize the use and added value of syndicated research on daily basis
Liaise with other departments to define measures and methods to evaluate their business performance and customer behavior, as well as deliver integrated insight solutions for the company
Execute consumer research studies to consistently provide actionable issue-specific, timely guidance for planning and decision making
Consolidate and review previously conducted market research to identify consumer insight
Help develop analysis plans, methods, solutions to help company achieve their customer strategies and business objectives to meet existing and developing company’ needs
Support development and delivery of regular insight reports, i.e. competitor activities scanning and impact analysis and key indicator analysis
Develop ways to integrate client loyalty data with the wide range of other marketing data
Heavily involved in all company’ project, from research request to establishing research plan to the actual company research and survey activities (i.e. project development based on products analysis)
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree (min.) in marketing and business management is highly preferable
At least 8 years of marketing experiences, preferably in life insurance industry
Deep knowledge in marketing applications with great computer literacy
Vast strategic and commercial skills to develop solutions that serve company’ needs
Excellent knowledge in customer level analysis, segmentation and modelling solutions
Good understanding of research application and data to business applications, including: pricing, promotions and marketing
Excellent analysis skills to apply marketing data to business and marketing strategies
Project management experience with good communications skills including the ability to build and deliver presentations to senior level executives
Proven track record in establish new solutions and development based on market data, with hands-on personality to define issues, opportunities, solutions, and practical executions
Ability to define market opportunity and strong knowledge of market trend, with the ability to work in a fast paced environment
Fluent in English, both written and oral
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.